    <!-- About Section -->
    <section id="about" class="about fade-in">
        <h2>About SafeSphere</h2>
        <p>We are a team of innovators passionate about bridging the gap between technology and everyday security needs. Our project, SafeSphere, was developed to provide affordable, reliable, and user-friendly security solutions tailored for individuals, families, and businesses.</p>
        <p>With expertise in embedded systems, electronics, and cybersecurity, we designed a multi-sensor perimeter security system that combines ultrasonic, PIR, and reed switch sensors with GSM technology for real-time alerts and remote control.</p>
        <h3>Our Vision & Mission</h3>
        <p><strong>Vision:</strong> To make smart security accessible to communities that cannot afford expensive commercial systems, while delivering a scalable solution that grows with user needs.</p>
        <p><strong>Mission:</strong> Empower individuals, families, and businesses to protect their spaces without the high cost of traditional systems.</p>
        <p><strong>Core Values:</strong> Innovation, Accessibility, Reliability, and Safety.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Features Section -->
    <section id="features" class="features fade-in">
        <h2>Smart Perimeter Security System</h2>
        <p>The system integrates ultrasonic, PIR, and reed switch sensors with the ATmega2560 microcontroller to monitor distance, motion, and access points. Detected anomalies trigger visual, audio, and GSM alerts. PIN authentication and remote arm/disarm via GSM ensure reliability, reduce false alarms, and provide affordable, scalable, and user-friendly perimeter security around your house.</p>
        <h3>Key Features</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i><strong>Multi-Sensor Detection:</strong> Ultrasonic for distance breaches, PIR for motion, and reed switches for door/window access.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-mobile-alt"></i><strong>Real-Time GSM Alerts:</strong> Receive instant notifications on your phone without needing internet.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-remote"></i><strong>Remote Control:</strong> Arm/disarm the system via SMS for two-way feedback.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-wifi-slash"></i><strong>No Internet Required:</strong> Works reliably in areas with poor connectivity, using GSM network.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-tools"></i><strong>Easy Installation:</strong> User-friendly setup for homes and businesses.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-expand-arrows-alt"></i><strong>Scalable Design:</strong> Future upgrades for IoT integration.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>System Process</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><i class="fas fa-play-circle"></i>System initialization and sensor monitoring.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>Detection of motion, distance breach, or door access.</li>
            <li><i class="fas fa-brain"></i>Microcontroller decision-making (safe, warning, intrusion).</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Benefits Section -->
    <section id="benefits" class="benefits fade-in">
        <h2>Why Choose SafeSphere?</h2>
        <p>SafeSphere addresses high intrusion rates with a low-cost solution that's not internet-dependent or prone to false alarms. It's affordable compared to commercial systems like Ring or Hikvision, providing peace of mind for cost-sensitive markets.</p>
        <h3>User Perspective</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><i class="fas fa-user"></i>Simple to use, provides peace of mind, no internet needed.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Business Perspective</h3>
